dexEntries.First Caught: Erbacub roams the forest gathering leaves and twigs, often seen tying them together with vines. It seems eager to prove itself, though its paws still tremble in battle.
Bearosion patrols forests like a ranger. Its safari hat never falls off, even during battle. It exudes leadership and calm strength.
Hileaph towers over the forest, wielding a fallen tree. Its wide-brim safari hat casts a long shadow, under which others gather for safety.
Sparcoon has a tail that glows brighter with its excitement, often setting the area around it aflame in its playful antics.
Blazuki glides across tall heights and long distances, leaving streaks of embers in the air. Its fiery mohawk flares up even further when it flies, warning others of its incoming presence.
Axolitl is often seen with its head dipped low. A mysterious crystal grows where its gills should be, making it difficult to lift its head above water. The crystal pulses faintly when it feels safe.
Axolote loses it’s once gentle movements and now have an alien quality to them. It now also appears to mutter to itself in an unknown language.

Axolarg towers above its foes, with a hulking physique sculpted by its crystalline armor. The only part of its body not encased in crystals is its head, and a floating crystal hovers above it, pulsing with mysterious energy.

Dribsom lurks in alleys and caves, its wings flapping silently as it watches from the shadows. Despite its small size, it’s known for stealing food and vanishing into the night sky with a hiss-like screech. They also pick on small prey in the nighttime.
